            "title": "Google 'Proudly' Defends Pentagon AI Ties Amid Internal Backlash: Report",
            "id": "4f884963-d7fd-4406-ac1e-61abc9ea4a0f",
            "description": "Alphabet Inc., the parent company of Google, has stated its commitment to working with the U.S. military, despite facing criticism internally. Kent Walker, Alphabet's President of Global Affairs, addressed employees in a memo, emphasizing Google's long-standing support for defense agencies. He mentioned that the company supports military uses of AI responsibly, excluding applications for domestic mass surveillance or autonomous weapons without human oversight. Walker defended this position by noting Google's involvement in classified government projects such as cybersecurity and veterans' healthcare. The company's stance aligns with other major AI labs. Alphabet did not respond immediately to Benzinga's request for comments. The full story is available on Benzinga.com.",
